job_history.work_description: Proactively initiate, develop, and manage long-term, profitable relationships. Manage existing client relationships to identify future needs and consultatively address them. Profile prospects and clients to identify additional financial needs and refer to appropriate financial partners. Deliver superior quality service in person or by phone such that client needs are met on a consistent, positive basis. Serve as primary contact for new account openings and cross sale of other products and services to clients and prospects.

Provide customer service by greeting, assisting and soliciting persons entering the office or on the telephone. Meet personal performance goals through handling complete loan cycle. Receive and process credit and employment verifications and records information obtained. Perform routine transactions at an on-line terminal. Process payments and disbursements.

Provide a superior client service experience while assisting in and supporting all aspects of service and sales-related activities in the branch. Develop new and strengthen/expand existing personal and business client relationships through daily client relationship management, providing financial solutions that meet clients' needs and goals, penetrating all product and service lines.

Floor Supervisor is an entry-level management position. A Floor Supervisor shares in the responsibility for the overall performance the store and assists Store Management with generating sales potential, recruiting and developing staff, maintaining store appearance, controlling expenses and shortages.

skills.name: Customer Service
skills.explanation: Has extensive experience in providing superior quality service to clients in person or by phone, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Sales
skills.explanation: Has experience in cross-selling products and services to clients and prospects, suggesting strong proficiency.

skills.name: Relationship Management
skills.explanation: Has developed and managed long-term, profitable relationships with clients, indicating strong proficiency.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Has experience as a Floor Supervisor, sharing responsibility for the overall performance of the store, showing a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Time Management
skills.explanation: Has handled multiple responsibilities, including client relationships, sales, and customer service, indicating a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Communication
skills.explanation: Has experience in communicating with clients and prospects to identify their needs and provide financial solutions, suggesting strong proficiency.

skills.name: Teamwork
skills.explanation: Has worked with Store Management to generate sales potential, recruit and develop staff, and maintain store appearance, showing a solid working proficiency.
